      'We are saved by grace, and true faith shows itself in love. The two are never opposed.',
    formationText:
      'Catholics believe we are saved by God\'s grace, received through faith. We cannot earn salvation. And yet Scripture is clear that genuine faith is alive and bears fruit. Saint James writes, "Faith apart from works is dead" (James 2:26), and Saint Paul speaks of "faith working through love" (Galatians 5:6).\n\nThere is no contradiction here. Good works do not buy God\'s love; they are the natural response of a heart that has received it. Grace comes first, always. Our love, our service, and our obedience are grace flowing outward.\n\nSo we never boast, and we never sit still. We let God\'s gift take hold of us and become visible in how we live.',
