    formationText: "The Church is honest that suffering is a mystery, not a math problem. God does not delight in our pain. He permits evil only because, in his wisdom and power, he can draw a greater good even out of it. We do not always see that good in this life, and we are allowed to grieve and to ask why.\n\nWhat God gives us is not mainly an explanation but a presence. He did not stay distant from our suffering. In Jesus, God entered it, and on the cross he transformed suffering from a dead end into a place where love can be poured out. United to Christ, even our pain can become meaningful and redemptive.",
    reflection: "Where is your suffering right now, and what would it mean to let Jesus be present in it rather than absent from it?",
