    title: "Is Genesis Literal? How Catholics Read Creation",
    category: "Scripture",
    summary: "Catholics are not forced to choose between Genesis and science. We read Scripture for the truth it means to teach.",
    formationText: "The Church teaches that the creation accounts in Genesis convey real, saving truths: that God alone created everything from nothing, that creation is good, and that human beings are made in his image. These truths are certain. Genesis is not, however, a scientific textbook, and it uses figurative, poetic language to teach who created and why, more than the exact how.\n\nSo a Catholic can hold the truths of Genesis with full faith while remaining free about scientific questions such as the age of the universe. Faith and reason both come from God and cannot truly contradict. What matters most is the heart of the message: behind all that exists is not chance, but a loving Creator.",
