    formationText: "In the ancient world, sacrifice expressed worship, thanksgiving, and sorrow for sin. God permitted and shaped Israel\u2019s sacrifices to teach deep truths: that sin is serious, that life is sacred, and that drawing near to a holy God requires atonement. Yet the prophets made clear that God desired mercy and a humble heart far more than the blood of animals.\n\nAll of it pointed forward. The Letter to the Hebrews teaches that those sacrifices could never truly take away sin; they were shadows of the real thing. Jesus is the Lamb of God who offers himself once for all. Every altar of the Old Testament was quietly preparing the world for the altar of the cross, made present at every Mass.",
