    formationText: "Scripture calls the fear of the Lord the beginning of wisdom. This is not the cringing fear of a slave before a tyrant. It is the awe a child feels before a parent they deeply love and respect, the sense that God is greater than us and that his ways are worthy of reverence. It keeps us humble and honest.\n\nThis holy fear grows into love, not away from it. As we know God better, our reverence deepens precisely because we see how good he is. The Church counts the fear of the Lord among the gifts of the Holy Spirit, a grace that helps us treasure our friendship with God and dread only the thought of turning from his love.",
    reflection: "Does God feel more like a distant judge or a holy Father you can revere and love at once?",
