    formationText: "Because Baptism is God\u2019s gift and not our achievement, it can be given even to those too young to ask for it, just as a newborn is loved long before it can love in return. From the earliest days, the apostles baptized whole households, and the Church has always understood this to include children. We do not make a child wait for grace any more than we make them wait for our love.\n\nBaptism frees from original sin, gives the life of grace, and makes the child a member of the Church. Parents and godparents then promise to raise the child in the faith, so that what was given freely can grow into a personal, living relationship with Christ. The child receives first; the yes of faith unfolds over a lifetime.",
