    formationText: "There are seasons when prayer feels dry and God seems far away. This is a normal and even important part of the spiritual life. Often God withdraws the comfort we feel so that our love can mature, learning to seek him for his own sake rather than for the good feelings. Elijah found that God was not in the wind or the fire, but in a still, small whisper.\n\nIn these times, the answer is not to stop praying but to stay, like a friend who keeps sitting with someone they love even in silence. Jesus himself cried out on the cross, my God, why have you forsaken me, and the Father had not abandoned him. Faithfulness in the silence is one of the purest forms of love.",
    reflection: "Can you keep showing up to God even when you feel nothing, trusting that he is nearer than he seems?",
