    formationText: "Scripture is clear that we contend not merely against flesh and blood but against spiritual forces of evil. The devil is real, a fallen angel who tempts and accuses, though he is only a creature, not a rival god, and his power is limited and already broken by the cross. Spiritual warfare is mostly ordinary: resisting temptation, choosing virtue, and refusing the lies that pull us from God.\n\nOur weapons are not dramatic but powerful: prayer, the sacraments, Scripture, humility, and trust. Saint James gives the strategy simply, submit to God, resist the devil, and he will flee. We do not fight in fear, because we fight from victory. Christ has already conquered, and we stand under his protection.",
    reflection: "What is one lie or temptation that pulls you from God, and which weapon, prayer, the sacraments, or Scripture, will you reach for?",
