    formationText: "Matthew, Mark, Luke, and John each present the one Gospel of Jesus Christ, but with different emphases for different communities. Matthew shows Jesus as the fulfillment of Israel's hope. Mark gives us a fast, urgent account of the suffering Servant. Luke highlights mercy and the poor. John soars into the mystery of Jesus as the eternal Word made flesh.\n\nThe Church received exactly these four as inspired and trustworthy. Far from contradicting one another, they enrich one another, the way several portraits of a beloved person reveal more than one ever could. Together they give us the full, living face of Jesus, so that we may believe and have life in his name.",
    reflection: "Which of the four Gospels are you drawn to right now, and what might Jesus want to show you through it?",
