    summary: "Jesus knew we are body and soul, so he gave us grace through things we can see, touch, and receive.",
    formationText: "God could have saved us in any way he chose. Instead, he came among us in the flesh, healing with mud and spittle, touching lepers, eating with sinners, and washing feet. After his Resurrection, Jesus did not leave us only with ideas and memories. He gave his Church the sacraments, sacred signs that truly give the grace they signify. Water, oil, bread, wine, words, and the laying on of hands become real channels of his life.\n\nThis fits how God made us. We are not pure spirits but persons of body and soul, who learn and love through what is physical. So Christ meets us in physical ways, and the sacraments become personal encounters with the risen Lord, who keeps acting through his Church. There are seven, given for the whole of life. Through them Jesus is not far away or only in the past. He reaches us now, again and again, with grace we can actually receive.",
    reflection: "Where in your life do you most need to encounter the grace of Christ in a concrete, real way?",
