    formationText: "Jesus told Nicodemus, unless one is born of water and the Spirit, he cannot enter the kingdom of God. Baptism is that new birth. It is not merely a public sign of a decision we have made. Something real happens: original sin and all personal sin are washed away, the Holy Spirit comes to dwell in us, and we are made true sons and daughters of God and members of his Church.\n\nSaint Paul says that in Baptism we are buried with Christ and raised with him to walk in newness of life. On the day of Pentecost, Peter told the crowd to repent and be baptized for the forgiveness of sins. Baptism is the doorway into the whole Christian life and the foundation on which everything else is built. If you are baptized, you already carry an astonishing dignity. Much of the journey of faith is simply learning to live what Baptism has already made you.",
